blog.title: kpop blog for when you're sad
blog.description: A random post blog. I write about Kpop, life, health, both physical and mental, and enjoy making people feel better and helping them out. I'll be your personal cheerleader! Check my page for my Kpop workouts that people seem to like :*

summary: Yo Kpop fandoms where you at
body:
Yo Kpop fandoms where you at

I really want to start projects for the planet using the huge platform Kpop fandoms have. I have witnessed their passions first hand as I am in a couple Kpop fandoms. But please! If I get enough people interested I’m willing to change my whole blog and make a new Twitter account to help guide people and create free project ideas to help the community and planet, because I’m very passionate about saving the earth.

Imagine one day becoming so corporative and spread out that your band’s fandom makes the news somewhere or an article is written because of something great you did. That is honestly my dream, working with people to help the planet and others. And I think fandoms have SO much potential, they are passionate, kind, loving, energetic, accepting and so much more.

This isn’t for clout or to get attention, I genuinely want to rally people together to make a change. I don’t care about myself or social media. I care about helping.
